  "texts": [
    "Looking first on raters' evaluation of effectiveness, we found a significant interaction between the source of the reappraisal (human or GPT-4) and the label (no label or label) such that the gap in reappraisal effectiveness between GPT and humans decreased when we added labels of the source to the reappraisals (b = -0.12, t(24254) = -2.03, p =.043, R 2 =.04, 95% CI [-0.24, 0.00]).",
    "Further exploring the difference in the effect of labels within each reappraisal source, we found that GPT reappraisals without labels were evaluated as more effective compared to GPT reappraisals with labels (b = -.18, t(1509) = -2.185, p =.029, R 2 = 0.04, 95% CI [-0.35, -0.02]).",
    "On the other hand, human",
    "EXPLORING HUMAN AND AI EMOTIONAL SUPPORT reappraisal quality was not affected by having a label (b = -0.061, t(501) = -0.95, p =.341, R 2 = 0.04, 95% CI [-0.19, 0.06].",
    "This lack of difference in the human condition is also an indication that participants were assuming that reappraisals were produced by humans."
  ],
